The paper deals with distributed control of discrete-event systems (DES), which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY). The use of heterarchical supervisor synthesis and partial-observation local controllers suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The paper also deals with large-scale systems, which may involve distributed computing (cs.DC) and possibly machine learning for scalability (cs.LG).
